# CODEOWNERS — solo/small-team mode
# Install to: .github/CODEOWNERS
#
# DESIGN: deliberately SPARSE. GitHub won't let a PR author approve their own
# PR, so any path owned by a team containing only you is permanently
# self-blocking. List ONLY Tier-3 paths, owned by {{SECOND_KEY_TEAM}} — a team
# containing only your second approver (do NOT add yourself).
#
# Pair with branch protection: require PRs, required approvals = 0, require
# review from Code Owners = ON. Verify with test PRs (see
# docs/branch-protection-checklist.md). NO global "*" rule.

# Protect the enforcement mechanism itself — keep these three.
/.github/                       {{SECOND_KEY_TEAM}}
/.claude/settings.json          {{SECOND_KEY_TEAM}}
/.claude/hooks/                 {{SECOND_KEY_TEAM}}

# CUSTOMIZE: your Tier-3 paths (same list as the hook and the CI GATED list).
# /src/auth/                    {{SECOND_KEY_TEAM}}
# /db/migrations/               {{SECOND_KEY_TEAM}}
# /src/remote-exec/             {{SECOND_KEY_TEAM}}
# /src/regulated-domain/        {{SECOND_KEY_TEAM}}

# Everything else is intentionally UNOWNED: merges on green CI plus your
# signed Change Record (see docs/change-record-template.md).
